Class Triangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.henrique.triangle.Triangle

  • public class Triangle
extends java.lang.Object

    • Constructor Detail

      • Triangle

        public Triangle​()
        Initialize a triangle with "1" on each side.

      • Triangle

        public Triangle​(double coteAB,
                double coteBC,
                double coteCA)
        Initialize a triangle with the values passed as parameters. If there is any problem with any parameters, it will create a Triangle default (with "1" on each side)
        Parameters:
        coteAB - Parameter to set the AB side
        coteBC - Parameter to set the BC side
        coteCA - Parameter to set the CA side

      • Triangle

        public Triangle​(double a,
                double b,
                double c,
                TriangleBuilder builder)
        Initialize a triangle with the values and rules passed as parameters. If there is any problem with any parameters, it will create a Triangle default (with "1" on each side)
        Exemple:
        Triangle(double coteAB, double coteBC, double angleB)
        Triangle(double coteAB, double coteCA, double angleB)
        Triangle(double coteBC, double coteCA, double angleB)
        Triangle(double coteAB, double angleB, double angleA)
        Triangle(double coteCA, double angleB, double angleA)
        Triangle(double coteBC, double angleB, double angleA)
        Parameters:
        a - Parameter to be used in the generic rule
        b - Parameter to be used in the generic rule
        c - Parameter to be used in the generic rule
        builder - Generic rule of creation of the triangle
        See Also:
        TriangleBuilder

      • setCotes

        public void setCotes​(double coteAB,
                     double coteBC,
                     double coteCA)
        Set the sides If there is any problem with any parameters, it will create a Triangle default (with "1" on each side)
        Exemple:
        t.setCotes(7.5, 8.5, 9.5);
        t.setCotes(10, 10, 10);
        t.setCotes(0, 0, 0);
        Parameters:
        coteAB - Parameter to set the AB side
        coteBC - Parameter to set the BC side
        coteCA - Parameter to set the CA side
